    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1880-08-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1880-08-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="253"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d253">
                <head>No. 253.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Outrey</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-08-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 14, 1880</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your note of the 20th of June last,
                    communicating the invitation of the minister of war of France to this Government
                    to designate officers of its Army to witness certain maneuvers, on a large
                    scale, of the French troops which are to take place this autumn, and referring
                    also to the reply of the 30th of June last of this Department to your note, I
                    now have the honor to inform you that the Secretary of War, in pursuance of the
                    kind invitation of your government, has detailed Maj. A. P. Morrow, of the Ninth
                    Cavalry, First Lieut. William H. Bixby, of the Engineer Corps, and First Lieut.
                    Rogers Birnie, jr., of the Ordnance Department, to witness the maneuvers in
                    question.</p>
                <pb facs="0489" n="389" xml:id="pg_389"/>
                <p>I beg you to do me the favor of conveying this information to your government,
                    and of thanking it, on behalf of the Secretary of War, for its courteous
                    invitation.</p>
                <p>Accept, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JOHN HAY,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
